 I couldn't take all three of them so I was running hoping they would eventually turn on each other, and the SKs had completely dispelled me and debuffed me by the time we were all forced to the middle.  In addition to the CCs, by that point I had used Lay Hands and one SoulFire charge to heal the HTs/lifetaps and melee damage I had taken.<br><br>I lucked out, because one of the SKs went LD at that point and was deemed disqualified when he returned.  The monk was at 40 health so I decided to get at least get one more kill before I died.  I think I used one more SoulFire charge and the rest of my mana during that battle (SK beating on my back while I finished off the monk).  Then I turned on the last SK, still with 3 SoulFire charges left.  I think I used one more charge while dispatching him. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I wasn't aware at that point that the last SK was disqualified so I had turned on him, and he actually did kill me after I went completely oom and used up my remaining SoulFire charges.  Keep in mind though that when I started in on him, he was full health and most likely full mana and fully buffed, since I don't think anyone had done much to him before that point.  He is also reputedly the best dueler in the guild--I didn't face him in the elimination rounds because our 60 epic mage managed to beat him.<br><br>It was a lot of fun, and a lot of people said they learned a lot about PvP in the process (many of these people had only dueled once or twice before).  One person watching said &quot;Wow, I'm starting a Paladin tomorrow&quot;.<br><br>I'm sure this won't be my last dueling experience. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Aalek</a><BR>60 Crusader<BR>Reign in Power<BR>Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utelkardawnbringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Telkar Dawnbringer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/26/02 1:03:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks for the tips</span><hr size=1> Lol that brings a tear to my eye <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Good to hear that, good to see peeps acknowledging what Pally's can do, as so often people pass us over as pushovers.  Gratz on your win! <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=269056" target="_blank">Telkar Dawnbringer</a><BR>51 Cavalier<BR>Master potter & wanna-be-crusader.....At least I've got the potter part down. </p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showPrevMessage?topicID=9.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showNextMessage?topicID=9.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=1><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.emailToFriend?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image